title: BAP Candidate Muhammad Sadiq Sanjrani wins PB-32
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Balochistan Awami Party (BAP) candidate Muhammad Sadiq Sanjrani won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-32 Chagai by securing 19,091 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI) candidate Mir Amanullah Natezi who bagged 17,178 votes.
Votersâ€™ turn-out remained at 43.69 per cent.
